@greptileai I believe this is also a false positive. `normalizeProviderId("github-copilot")` returns `"github-copilot"` unchanged — there is no alias mapping for it:

```ts
export function normalizeProviderId(provider: string): string {
  const normalized = provider.trim().toLowerCase();
  if (normalized === "z.ai" || normalized === "z-ai") return "zai";
  if (normalized === "opencode-zen") return "opencode";
  if (normalized === "qwen") return "qwen-portal";
  if (normalized === "kimi-code") return "kimi-coding";
  return normalized; // ← "github-copilot" passes through
}
```

The test stub `find("github-copilot", "claude-opus-4.5")` matches exactly what the resolver calls. Confirmed by running the test — all 11 tests in `model.test.ts` pass.
